<font color="#FF0000">CHRONOLOGY OF THE VIETNAM WAR</font><br>
<tt>Thu Jan 23  1:46:22 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Thailand (when I was there TDY) by Chester L. Cooper entitled &quot;The Lost Crusade, America in Vietnam.&quot;  It has a foreward by W. Averell Harriman, and cWow, I'm impressed with Professor Grivetti's efforts here.  'Wish I was closer, but I'm up in Oregon.<br><br>
In one of your postings, Prof. Grivetti, you mentioned needing a chronology of events in Vietnam.  I happen to have a book I bought in the book store in either DaNang or ontains a comprehensive chronology of events from &quot;September 2, 1945--Ho Chi Minh proclaims Republic of Vietnam&quot; to July 1, 1970--President Nixon names Ambassador Bruce chief U.S. delegate to Paris talks.&quot; In between are 50 pages of chronology.  The book was published by Dodd, Mead &amp; Company, New York, and is copyrighted 1970, ISBN 0-396-06241-5, Library of Congress Catalog Card Number: 79:135539.  It also states &quot;Printed in the United States of America by The Cornwall Press, Inc., Cornwall, N.Y.<br><br>
The interesting part was that I read this book while on combat air duty with the 37th Aerospace Rescue and Recovery Squadron in DaNang.  I still have it, torn cover and all, here in my library.  Best wishes, and keep up the good work.
